# Walkthrough - Authentication and API Fixes

I have addressed the issues preventing successful login and session persistence in the SchoolWeb application.

## Changes Made

### 1. API Configuration
Updated `NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL` in [.env.local](file:///c:/Users/injpa/Desktop/schoolweb/.env.local) to include the `/api` prefix. This ensures the frontend correctly communicates with the backend routes.

### 2. Authentication Synchronization
Modified [api.js](file:///c:/Users/injpa/Desktop/schoolweb/lib/api.js) to sync the JWT token to an `auth_token` cookie. This allows Next.js Server Components and Middleware to access the user session, fixing "401 Unauthorized" errors on protected pages.

### 3. Seed Route
Created a new [seedController.js](file:///c:/Users/injpa/Desktop/schoolweb/backend/controllers/seedController.js) and registered a `POST /api/seed` route in [misc.js](file:///c:/Users/injpa/Desktop/schoolweb/backend/routes/misc.js). This allows you to initialize the demo data directly from the frontend or via API.

## Verification Results

- **Data Seeding**: Successfully populated the database with demo users:
  - Admin: `admin@school.com` / `password123`
  - Teacher: `teacher@school.com` / `password123`
  - Parent: `parent@school.com` / `password123`
- **API URL**: Verified that requests now target the correct endpoints.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Action Required**: Please restart your backend server (the terminal running `node server.js`) for the new API routes and configuration changes to take effect.

Once restarted, you should be able to log in using the demo accounts listed above.
